alt="A simple website design."
/>
</picture></div></div><div
class="block-intro-text"><p>One thing I've noticed reviewing websites is that good sites do not need to be complex. In fact, oftentimes sites that are complex, either providing much more information than is necessary or using complicated elements such as animations, end up being confusing for site visitors.</p><p>Simple websites can be easy to create and must be easy to understand without sacrificing the essentials. A hotel website, for example, can be simple, but it must still provide a way for site visitors to book a room. I've reviewed five sites that accomplish the essential goals of a site in its niche while being easy to build and navigate. If you're looking to create one of your own, try <a
href="/">Zarla's AI website builder</a>.</p></div><div
class="mt-0 mt-md-2 entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="block-wrapper"><div
class="block block-heads-up"><div
