class="row"><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-makes-a-simple-website-good class="question">What makes a simple website good?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Using the least amount of text and elements while retaining the core functions necessary for a website in its niche.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-a-website-be-too-simple class="question">Can a website be too simple?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>If the site sacrifices important information or functionality for simplicity, it's probably too simple. For example, a website for a clothing store shouldn't eliminate pricing or a shopping cart</p></div></div><div
